job_history.work_description: Perform professional administrative work involving the development, administration, and coordination of a comprehensive series of training and development opportunities for University staff and faculty.
Trained over 250 time keepers on time keeping techniques and best practices, conducting workshops and one-on-one coaching sessions that contributed to a successful implementation of PeopleSoft.
Responsible for the overall business performance of managing the restaurant and training all new employees.

skills.name: Training and Development
skills.explanation: Has extensive experience in developing, administering, and coordinating training programs for staff and faculty, indicating expert-level mastery.

skills.name: Time Management
skills.explanation: Trained over 250 time keepers on time keeping techniques and best practices, suggesting strong proficiency in time management.

skills.name: Leadership
skills.explanation: Held multiple leadership roles, including HR Manager and Restaurant Manager, indicating strong proficiency in leadership.

skills.name: Coaching
skills.explanation: Conducted one-on-one coaching sessions for time keepers, suggesting strong proficiency in coaching.

skills.name: Project Management
skills.explanation: Contributed to the successful implementation of PeopleSoft, showing a solid working proficiency in project management.

skills.name: Communication
skills.explanation: Effectively communicated training and development opportunities to staff and faculty, indicating a solid working proficiency in communication.

skills.name: PeopleSoft
skills.explanation: Involved in the implementation of PeopleSoft, but the extent of proficiency is unclear.
